name: Zoe Place Liverpool
summary: The closure of Zoe's Place, a baby hospice in Liverpool, has sent shockwaves through the local community. The hospice, which has provided care for critically ill infants for 29 years, will shut its doors later this year. Families are devastated by the news, as they have nowhere else to turn for the specialized care and support that Zoe's Place provides. Other hospices in the area have pledged their support, but it is unclear if they will be able to meet the high demand for services. The closure of Zoe's Place is a significant loss for Liverpool, and it will have a profound impact on the lives of the families who have relied on its services.
